# Task list sync (TheaterOrStream)

At the **start of every session** (especially after `git pull` or when the user says they worked from phone):

## 1. Discover what changed

Run in parallel:
- `git log --oneline -15`
- `git diff origin/main...HEAD` (or `git log origin/main..HEAD`) if behind/ahead
- Skim recent commits for task IDs: `fix-upcoming-db`, `slim-hydration`, `edge-read-api`, `db-migrations`, `server-tmdb-proxy`, etc.

Phone-only work (Supabase SQL Editor, Vercel env, manual deploy) may **not** appear in git — ask or infer from user notes.

## 2. Update ALL four task sources together

Never update only one file. Sync these in the same pass:

| Source | Path |
|--------|------|
| Repo master plan | `.agent/tos-production-architecture-plan.md` |
| Work log | `.agent/implementation-work-log.md` |
| API plan cross-ref | `.agent/implementation-plan-api-optimization.md` |
| Cursor plan | `~/.cursor/plans/tos_production_architecture_e5360011.plan.md` |

## 3. What to update on each task change

- YAML frontmatter `todos[].status`: `completed` | `pending`
- Master table: ✅ Done · 🔄 Partial · ⬜ Pending
- Phase 1 checkboxes `[x]` / `[ ]` where applicable
- **HEAD** line → current `git log -1 --oneline` short hash
- **Progress** count (e.g. `4 / 14`)
- Work log: task section + git history table for new commits

## 4. Marking complete

When a task is done (code merged, or user confirms Supabase/Vercel work):
- Tick ✅ in all tables
- Set YAML `status: completed`
- Add summary row under "Completed" in work log
- Move "Next recommended" to the following pending task

Partial work (e.g. `unify-content-api`): use 🔄 and note what remains.

## 5. Do not

- Leave Cursor plan stale while repo docs are updated
- Mark `db-migrations` or SQL tasks complete without user confirmation when run outside git
- Skip sync after the user mentions phone, pull, or "I finished X"
